# Vercel Web Analytics Implementation

Successfully implemented Vercel Web Analytics for the Next.js App Router project.

## Changes Made

### 1. Installed @vercel/analytics Package
- Used npm to install `@vercel/analytics` package (version 2.0.0)
- Generated and updated `package-lock.json` for dependency consistency

### 2. Modified app/layout.tsx
- Added import statement: `import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/next'`
- Wrapped the layout content with proper HTML structure (`<html>` and `<body>` tags)
- Added `<Analytics />` component inside the `<body>` tag after `{children}`
- Preserved the existing `ClerkProvider` wrapper and all existing functionality

### 3. Build Verification
- Ran `npm run build` successfully
- Build completed without errors
- Type checking passed
- Linting passed (Next.js includes linting in the build process)
- All 11 static pages generated successfully

## Files Modified

- **app/layout.tsx**: Added Analytics component import and component placement
- **package.json**: Added @vercel/analytics dependency
- **package-lock.json**: Created with all dependency information

## Implementation Notes

- This is an App Router project (Next.js 15.3.6) using the `app` directory
- The layout was minimal, wrapping only ClerkProvider, so I added the proper HTML structure (`<html>` and `<body>` tags) as required by Next.js App Router
- The Analytics component is placed at the end of the body, which is the recommended position for performance
- No tests were found in the project, so testing was limited to build verification
- All existing functionality is preserved, including Clerk authentication

